The World Health Organisation, WHO has revealed countries with the highest number of COVID-19 cases in the world. The WHO disclosed that the United States, US, Brazil and India have the highest increasing cases of COVID-19 cases in the world, Reuters reports. It also said that as of Saturday COVID-19 cases rose to 212,326 in 24 hours. According to the WHO daily report: “The biggest increases were from the United States, Brazil and India.” COVID-19 cases were 189,077 on June 28 and deaths have remained steady at about 5,000 a day. Reuters had reported that the virus increase around the world had exceeded 11 million on Friday.